                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 183.7/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-18T13:50:00+00:00"
                            >January 18, 1919—1:50 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>323. [From <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName>.] Your 281 January 17th
                    4 p.m. There was never any question regarding representation of Roumania at the
                    Peace Conference. With unanimous approval she has been assigned two
                    representatives.</p>
                <p>Same information sent to <persName corresp="#p_VCJ1">Vopicka</persName> through
                    Embassy here, referring to joint telegram from Allied Ministers Jassy, dated
                    Bucharest January 7th. <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
